</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1437,151,573]" pageId="12" pageNumber="154">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,262,475,501]" pageId="12" pageNumber="154">Note.</emphasis>
The shape of pronotum and the body size can vary within certain limits in extant representatives of the tribe. The main diagnostic characters for species limitation within the extinct genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Alekseev et Pankowski" authorityYear="2020" box="[1119,1234,511,537]" class="Insecta" family="Melandryidae" genus="Madelinia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="154" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1119,1234,511,537]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="154">Madelinia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is considered the pubescence, the shape of scutellar shield and the comparative lenghts of metatarsomeres 1–2.
</paragraph>
